results.name: Yeezy Slides 'Resin'
results.story: The Yeezy Slide 'Resin' showcases Kanye West’s minimalist interpretation of an athletic sandal. A monochromatic finish in a subtle green hue is applied to the slip-on silhouette, constructed from EVA foam for lightweight durability. The footbed delivers added comfort with a soft top layer, etched with adidas’ three-stripe branding at the heel. Underfoot, the outsole is formed with horizontal grooves for enhanced traction.

results.name: Yeezy Slides 'Bone'
results.story: The Yeezy Slide 'Bone' applies a neutral hue to Kanye West’s take on an everyday sandal, constructed from EVA foam for lightweight comfort. The minimalist design is good for a sleek, contemporary look, with exterior branding limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed at the heel of the footbed. The slip-on build rides atop a high-traction outsole, fitted with strategically placed grooves for sure footing.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Bone'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Bone’ applies a monochromatic Off-White finish to the minimalist slip-on sandal, constructed from molded EVA foam for lightweight comfort. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo, debossed at the base of the contoured footbed. A series of deep horizontal grooves are built into the outsole, good for enhanced traction and flexibility with each step.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Azure'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure’ utilizes a re-engineered Primeknit upper finished in muddy brown tones. A contrasting splash of royal blue distinguishes the translucent monofilament window that’s woven into the lateral side of the sock-like construction. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a fluid transition. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Enflame
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Enflame’ spotlights the sneaker’s adiPRENE+ tooling with a vibrant orange finish. Offering a blend of impact absorption and responsive cushioning, the podular midsole is directly inspired by the adidas KB8 3, released in 1999 as Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe. Up top, the sneaker’s complex build combines brown open mesh with soft suede overlays in tan, grey and indigo. A rubber midfoot wrap provides added durability and support.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Bone'
results.story: The Yeezy Slide Infant 'Bone' dropped in December 2019 as part of a Yeezy sandal collection made for the whole family. Finished in an understated and neutral hue, the miniature slip-on differs from its full-sized counterpart by adding an adjustable strap at the heel for an extra secure fit. The soft yet durable foam build rides atop a ripple outsole, good for added traction and comfort.

results.name: Yeezy Slides 'Desert Sand'
results.story: The Yeezy Slide 'Desert Sand' offers Kanye West’s take on a casual sandal, good for postgame relaxation or weekend lounging. A subtle tan finish complements the minimalist build, made with lightweight and durable EVA foam. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the soft footbed. The outsole is crafted with strategically placed horizontal grooves for superior comfort and traction.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Lmnte'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Lmnte’ features a contrasting blend of brown and slate hues on a breathable Primeknit upper designed to wrap around the foot in lightweight support. A yellow finish is applied to the translucent monofilament window that cuts through the lateral side, complete with a series of large perforations for enhanced air flow. Underfoot, cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole reveals the sneaker’s full-length Boost cushioning.

results.name: Air Yeezy 'Grammy' Prototype
results.story: Like most sneakers that hit production, Kanye’s first Air Yeezy with Nike was unveiled in a prototype offering that varied slightly from his official first signature shoe with the Swoosh. This shoe is constructed with a high-top design that incorporates a primarily black leather offering with perforated panels throughout the vamp and tongue. Contrasted with a glow-in-the-dark outsole, the shoe also incorporates a translucent red lace-lock with tonal branding throughout. A midfoot strap is included for a locked-in fit.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 fuses the German brand's retro design principles and Kanye West's affinity for future-forward industrialism. Rendered in Stone mesh, this iteration—issued in November 2019—hosts tonal leather and suede panels, matching laces threaded through a tongue overlay and reflective piping. The sneaker utilizes a distinctive midsole with Adiprene technology for cushioned support and a curved gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy 700 V3 'Arzareth'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Arzareth’ features vibrant blue tones on a breathable knit upper, its side panels overlaid with a semi-translucent RPU cage for added structure and durability. Contrasting black is applied to the sneaker’s bootie-style collar, good for a snug fit around the ankle. The sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: Yeezy 500 High 'Sumac'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 High ‘Sumac’ treats the bulky silhouette to a unique palette made up of rich earth tones and sharply contrasting primary colors. The upper is constructed from brown mesh with tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. They’re joined by midfoot suede overlays in blue and indigo, along with bold a crimson overlay that wraps around the collar and snakes underneath the stitched-on eyelets. The sneaker is mounted on a podular adiPRENE+ that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium
results.story: A performance basketball shoe envisaged by Kanye West, the adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Barium’ features a dull green Primeknit upper overlaid with semi-translucent detailing for a fluid, dynamic look. Black no-sew overlays at the toe and heel provide seamless, lightweight support, while interior bootie construction deliver a snug fit. The sneaker rides atop a caged Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum 'Flash Orange' carries a breathable jacquard mesh upper with wavy overlays in contrasting black and burnt orange accents. The mid-top is equipped with a stretchy neoprene collar and fortified with a synthetic suede toe cap. A seamless heel counter extends to the midsole, packed with full-length Boost cushioning wrapped in a semi-translucent rubber cage. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a classic herringbone tread for stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Pepper'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Pepper’ applies a neutral color scheme to its breathable Primeknit upper, featuring a snug, sock-like fit that allows for a secure fit with or without laces. A muddy tan finish distinguishes the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, allowing the signature detail to stand out against a knit backdrop in lighter grey and Off-White tones. A full-length Boost midsole supports the lightweight build, equipped with a raised heel for a smooth ride.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Resin'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Resin’ showcases a subtle monochromatic finish on a minimalist sandal constructed from lightweight EVA foam. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo, debossed on the plush top layer of the footbed. A series of strategically placed flex grooves are utilized on the outsole, providing a combination of grippy traction and impact absorption with each step.

results.name: Yeezy 450 'Dark Slate'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

results.name: Yeezy 500 'Taupe Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 ‘Taupe Light’ steps out in an understated monochromatic colorway that allows the sneaker’s premium construction to come to the fore. Open mesh makes up the majority of the upper, fortified with cow suede and leather overlays throughout. Reflective piping around the eyelets provides a hi-vis element, while a rubber midfoot wrap offers enhanced durability. The layered build is supported by an adiPRENE+ midsole inspired by Kobe Bryant’s third signature shoe, the adidas KB8 3.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Alien'
results.story: Revising Kanye West's seminal design, the adidas Yeezy Boost 380 'Alien' distinguishes itself by thinking beyond the futuristic quality that defined its predecessor. Its sleek textile upper is engineered with a textured weave pattern mimicking an extraterrestrial landscape and reflectivity for visual depth. A similar lacing structure snakes up the higher-cut bootie. Boost tech is encased in a milky translucent rubber that's also extended to the outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Salt
results.story: The Yeezy 500 ‘Salt’ sticks with the same monochromatic design used on previous colorways of the bulky lifestyle silhouette. Here, a light grey shade is applied to the layered upper, built with a combination of cow suede, premium leather, mesh and nubuck accents. A rubber wrap atop the midsole provides added durability while reflective trim around the eyelets provide visibility in low-light conditions.

results.name: Yeezy Basketball 'Quantum' Sample
results.story: Marking his first foray into a hoops-inspired sneaker, the adidas Yeezy Basketball 'Quantum' brings Kanye West's avant-garde design language into a more functional design. This version's upper is divided up with a lace-up neoprene bootie, snakeskin-textured paneling and a suede toe. Reflective elements beam under the mesh side inserts and on the heel. A semi-translucent casing contains responsive Boost cushioning, doubling as the outsole for directional traction.

results.name: Yeezy Slides 'Earth Brown'
results.story: The Yeezy Slides ‘Earth Brown’ showcase a subdued monochromatic finish on the slip-on design. Built for everyday wear, the versatile sandal is constructed from EVA foam with a molded footbed for immediate step-in comfort. Underfoot, the outsole uses exaggerated flex grooves for enhanced traction. This pair dropped alongside accompanying colorways in ‘Bone,’ ‘Resin’ and ‘Desert Sand,’ with the latter available exclusively at Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply site.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Blush
results.story: Initially released in February 2018 as a limited pre-order in New York and Los Angeles, the Yeezy 500 ‘Blush’ underwent a general release in April 2018. Its moniker is a fitting one, as the monochromatic light taupe finish barely registers as a color. The subdued palette is contrasted by a bold silhouette, featuring a paneled mesh and suede upper combined with a hefty midsole reminiscent of adidas’ Feet You Wear' technology of the 1990s.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Resin'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infant ‘Resin’ combines a minimalist, futuristic design with lightweight comfort. A monochromatic olive green finish is applied to the slip-on silhouette, constructed from injected EVA foam and equipped with an adjustable heel strap that wraps around the back of the foot for an extra secure fit. Deep horizontal grooves are built into the outsole for enhanced cushioning and traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Safflower
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Safflower’ showcases a mostly neutral color scheme in keeping with the Yeezy brand’s signature palette. Subtle hints of color arrive via yellow striations throughout the monofilament engineered mesh upper, overlaid with a glow-in-the-dark RPU cage that extends from heel to toe. The sneaker’s interior bootie construction is rendered in a contrasting black finish, offering a snug, comfortable fit. A PU encapsulated EVA midsole anchors the streamlined silhouette.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Enflame Amber'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Enflame Amber’ features muted earth tones on the upper, constructed from breathable beige mesh with dark brown suede overlays throughout the midfoot. A tonal beige toe cap reinforces an unexpected pop of blue mesh on the toe box. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a coral-hued EVA carrier and made visible through cut-out detailing on the herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Covellite (Infants)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Covellite’ offers sock-like comfort for growing feet. Finished in varying blue shades, the re-engineered Primeknit upper is equipped with no-tie stretch laces for easy on and off. A translucent monofilament window is woven directly into the knit construction for textural depth and added breathability. The sneaker sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced with wrapped sidewalls and a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 380 Covellite (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Covellite’ gets its name from a blue mineral composed of sulfide copper. Like its inspiration, the shoe features an exterior surface finished in a craggy texture and varying blue shades. The re-engineered Primeknit upper is accented with decorative no-tie stretch laces and a translucent monofilament window woven into the side panel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a wrapped Boost midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone tread gum rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Bone White
results.story: Kanye West and adidas revisit the Yeezy 500, this time in a 'Bone White' colorway. This August 2019 edition follows the silhouette's established, chunky silhouette with a cow suede, premium leather and mesh upper in Off-White tones. As in colorways past, this edition includes reflective piping details and the unmistakable, retro basketball midsole design. adidas adiPRENE+ cushioning pairs underfoot with contoured rubber pods to promote traction.

results.name: Nike Air Yeezy 1 Blink
results.story: The Air Yeezy ‘Blink’ from April 2009 is one of three sneakers that kicked off Kanye West’s partnership with Nike. The high-top blends a variety of materials and textures on the upper, finished in tonal black with a pop of bright pink on the lining, lace lock, and ‘Yeezy’ print on the heel loop. While the vamp features smooth suede construction, the midfoot strap and heel panel are covered in an all-over ‘Y’ print for an eye-catching texture.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Magnet
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 is a combination of heritage functionality and Kanye West's unorthodox design style. Launched in September 2019, this Magnet version is engineered with a neoprene, suede and leather build in a palette of grey gradients. Reflective accents remain at the heel for visual interest in low light. The sculpted Boost-filled midsole flaunts defined pops of color while gum rubber for the outsole exudes throwback appeal.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Alvah
results.story: The Yeezy 700 V3 'Alvah' delivers a stealthy colorway of Kanye West’s sculpted silhouette. A black and grey mesh upper is fortified with glow-in-the-dark RPU overlays for structural support. Interior bootie construction is good for a snug, comfortable fit, while reflective accents at the base of the tongue deliver added visibility in low-light conditions. Forgoing Boost cushioning, the sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Hylte
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ features an eye-catching color scheme that strays from the signature Yeezy palette, which traditionally leans heavily on muted earth tones. A splash of fluorescent green is applied to the the sneaker’s translucent monofilament window, contrasted by the camo-like tan and yellow composition that makes up the Primeknit upper. Standard Boost cushioning is enveloped in grey rubber and reinforced with a herringbone-traction outsole. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Hylte Glow'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Hylte Glow’ showcases a tan Primeknit upper blended with neon yellow detailing treated to a glow-in-the-dark finish. An unexpected splash of lime green is applied to the signature monofilament window, allowing the semi-translucent panel to stand out on the sneaker’s lateral side. The sock-like build rides on a caged Boost midsole, visible underfoot through cut-out detailing on the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Turtledove
results.story: First seen on Kanye and his models at the Yeezy Season 1 fashion show in February 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Turtle Dove’ was the second shoe released in the adidas Yeezy collection after the Yeezy Boost 750 ‘OG.’ Dropped on June 27, 2015, the ‘Turtle Dove’ sold out instantly online and was eventually anointed 2015’s Shoe of the Year at the Footwear News 29th Annual Achievement Awards.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Clear Brown
results.story: The adidas Yeezy PowerPhase deviates from Kanye West's future-thinking design ethos in a minimalist look inspired by retro court style. Unveiled in September 2019, this iteration in Clear Brown leather features perforated Three-Stripes, tonal lacing and a foil gold 'Calabasas' imprint. The signature logo window lends a touch of color via the Trefoil. Its split EVA and rubber cupsole stays true to the sneaker's vintage inspiration.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 Moonrock
results.story: Following the ‘Turtle Dove’ and ‘Pirate’ colorways, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moonrock’ features a moonrock/agate grey Primeknit upper and a moonrock Boost outsole. First previewed on Instagram by Kim Kardashian and released on November 14th, 2015, the Yeezy Boost 350 ‘Moon Rock’ was sold exclusively at stores that carried Yeezy Season One apparel.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM (Lifestyle Model)
results.story: The Yeezy Quantum 'Quantum' represents Kanye West’s debut sneaker in the basketball space. This lifestyle edition features a knit upper with wavy cut-out strips that reveal a breathable mesh base underneath. The grey and white tones used on both layers are complemented by reflective accents, an Off-White suede toe cap and solid black hits at the collar, tongue and heel. The mid-top is supported by a Boost midsole and a herringbone-tread rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Calcite Glow'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Calcite Glow’ highlights a neutral combination of white and grey tones on the breathable Primeknit upper, complete with camo-like glow-in-the-dark detailing that’s revealed when the lights go out. A dark grey finish distinguishes the translucent monofilament window on the sneaker’s side panel, matching the sock-like collar that provides a snug fit around the ankle. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning with each step.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Infant)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy 500 Infant ‘Stone’ applies a neutral finish to a layered build that combines a stretchy Lycra base with tonal overlays in cow suede and premium leather. Reflective piping adds a high-vis element to the monochromatic design, reinforced with an abrasion-resistant rubber wrap that runs along the base of the upper. A retro-inspired adiPRENE+ midsole rides on a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Abez'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Abez’ features a subtle mix of grey, silver and cream threads throughout the breathable Primeknit upper, arranged in various woven patterns for a distinctive patchwork effect. A yellowish tint suffuses the signature post-dyed monofilament side stripe that distinguishes the sneaker’s lateral profile. The lightweight build is supported by the 350 V2’s standard full-length Boost midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Soft Vision
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 meets at the intersection of the German brand's past technical concepts and designer Kanye West's pairing of industrial ethos meets fashion. Introduced in November 2019, this edition's full tonal look is presented in Soft Vision mesh, leather and suede. Its laces are threaded through a matching tongue overlay. Inspired by retro Feet You Wear technology, a rounded Adiprene midsole and gum rubber outsole bolster the underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas Grey
results.story: Kanye West and adidas took their collaborative line in a decidedly retro-inspired direction with the launch of their Yeezy Powerphase Calabasas, which launched December 2017 in this understated grey colorway. The versatile low-top is rendered in soft leather, finished in a dusty grey shade that also covers the shoe’s die-cut EVA midsole and rubber outsole. The quarter panel features perforated three-stripes, a logo window with adidas trefoil branding, and ‘CALABASAS’ in gold foil lettering.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Frozen Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Frozen Blue’ applies a burst of color to Kanye West’s basketball-inspired mid-top. The layered upper features a bright blue RPU cage atop a jacquard knit upper, reinforced with synthetic suede at the toe cap. Black neoprene on the collar and tongue offers stretchy comfort, while a seamless heel counter is good for improved stability. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Boost midsole reinforced with a semi-translucent TPU cage and a herringbone traction outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 Stone (Kids)
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids ‘Stone’ updates the chunky retro-inspired silhouette with a subdued monochromatic finish. The sneaker’s layered construction utilizes a blend of stretchy Lycra, soft cow suede and premium leather. Reflective piping offers added visibility in low-light conditions, while an abrasion-resistant rubber overlays wraps around the base of the upper, giving way to a podular midsole built with adiPRENE+ cushioning.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Rock
results.story: Borrowing elements from the chunky Yeezy 500, 2019's Yeezy Desert Boot 'Rock' is a futuristic, three-quarter boot. The upper features mesh with supple suede overlays, rope laces and an exaggerated mudguard. A thick foam midsole adds cushion, pairing with a rugged, outdoors-ready outsole. A sandy, military-type tone covers the silhouette, with just and embossed adidas logo on the bottom of the sole for branding.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Barium (Infants)
results.story: Made for little feet, the adidas Yeezy Quantum Infant ‘Barium’ features a seamless build that combines a grey jacquard knit base overlaid with a translucent RPU cage on the side panels. Reflective detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions, while a synthetic suede toe cap provides improved durability in a high-wear area. The sneaker rides on a Boost midsole enveloped in a semi-translucent TPU cage.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Teal Blue
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Teal Blue’ delivers a lifestyle variation of Kanye West’s performance hoops shoe, highlighted by a patterned knit upper that blends bright teal accents with varying shades of grey. A tonal suede overlay adds durability along the toe, while a pronounced heel counter in a contrasting black finish provides rearfoot support. Responsive cushioning is provided by a full-length Boost midsole encased in semi-translucent rubber.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Sun
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Sun’ treats the lifestyle runner to a lively color scheme that accentuates the silhouette’s multi-layered build. The majority of the mesh and leather upper is rendered in varying shades of yellow, contrasted by a black suede overlay that extends to mesh forefoot panels in blue and teal. A clashing coral finish is applied to the bulky midsole, featuring full-length drop-in Boost cushioning for a smooth ride. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole delivers optimal grip.

results.name: Yeezy 500 Kids 'Soft Vision'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Kids symbolizes Kanye West's directional design intent with a throwback influence. Updated in November 2019, this version has a mesh, cow suede and premium leather upper expressed in a monochromatic Soft Vision scheme. Reflective piping surrounds the lace eyelets and a protective mudguard wraps the sidewall. The sneaker tools a tonal midsole with Adiprene+ cushioning and a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Infant 'Desert Sand'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infant ‘Desert Sand’ brings a spartan aesthetic to little feet, highlighted by a monochromatic neutral finish on a lightweight EVA build. Unlike the sandal’s full-sized counterpart, this pair adds a hook-and-loop strap that wraps around the heel for a custom fit. Underfoot, the bold sawtooth outsole features deep flex grooves for improved impact absorption and traction.

results.name: Yeezy 500 Infant 'Bone White'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 500 Infant sneaker combines Kanye West's retro design style and the German brand's heritage technology dating back to the KB8 III. Issued in August 2019, this version carries a Bone White upper constructed of cow suede, premium leather and mesh with reinforced cord laces and reflective piping circling the eyelets. AdiPRENE+ midsole cushioning and a tonal rubber outsole balance impact reduction and grip.

results.name: adidas Yeezy QNTM Sea Teal
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Quantum ‘Sea Teal’ dresses the lifestyle silhouette in a breathable knit upper that blends mostly neutral grey and black tones with washed-out teal accents. A soft elastic collar provides a comfortable fit around the ankle, while the seamless heel counter is designed to hug the back of the foot for enhanced containment. A semi-translucent rubber cage shores up the full-length Boost midsole, supported underfoot by a herringbone-traction gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Kids 'Hylte'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Kids ‘Hylte’ delivers an eye-catching colorway of the minimalist slip-on silhouette. The re-engineered Primeknit upper is rendered in a mix of mustard yellow and honeyed tan hues, while the translucent monofilament window is distinguished by an eye-catching neon green finish. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in a grey rubber cage and supported by a herringbone rubber outsole. The Yeezy Boost 380 Kids 'Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 750 'Black' Sample
results.story: This blacked-out Yeezy Boost 750 Sample was unveiled in 2015 as the second-ever colorway following a two-tone grey version. The high-top silhouette’s suede construction is complemented by a matching midfoot canvas strap and Yeezy Boost midsole to give the shoe a tonal look.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Onyx
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Onyx Non-Reflective’ delivers a subdued rendition of the minimalist lifestyle sneaker. A charcoal grey finish dominates the re-engineered Primeknit upper, with inky black and a subtle streak of navy blue surrounding the translucent monofilament window. The sock-like build sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, encaged in semi-translucent rubber and supported underfoot by a herringbone traction outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Etham
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Sand’ delivers a monotone iteration of Kanye West’s clog-like silhouette. Featuring a slightly darker tan shade than the debut ‘Ararat’ colorway from 2020, the slip-on makes use of a flexible one-piece build that combines standard EVA with an algae-based foam compound. Multiple ventilation ports allow feet to breathe, while textured interiors offer no-slip grip. Underfoot, a classic herringbone tread provides dependable traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Chocolate
results.story: Released in October 2015 as part of Yeezy Season 1, the Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Chocolate’ features a silhouette that combines a duck boot with a military boot, wrapped up in a monochromatic build. The materials include rubber, ballistic mesh, and suede, all finished in the same dark brown palette. Exterior branding is limited to adidas and Yeezy wordmarks on the outsole, as well as the mismatched tongue tags.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Salt
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Salt’ follows a design trail originally blazed by the Yeezy 500 in November 2018. Like its predecessor, the lifestyle silhouette features a monochromatic light grey finish on a mesh base with tonal overlays in suede and leather. A sculpted midsole in matching grey, concealing full-length Boost cushioning within, features a subtle black accent, matched by the rubber outsole underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Inertia
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Inertia’ is part of the Yeezy Season 8 lineup that launched March 2019. The ‘Inertia’ colorway showcases the original 700 upper, with a heavily paneled construction made with premium suede, mesh and smooth leather sections. Cast primarily in cool grey tones, the sneaker includes hits of Tangerine for contrast. The shoe’s signature chunky midsole is equipped with full-length Boost cushioning for responsive comfort.

results.name: Nike Roshe Run FB Yeezy
results.story: The Nike Roshe One FB ‘Yeezy’ features a distinctive color palette reminiscent of the brand’s Solar Red Air Yeezy 2 collaboration with Kanye West. The shoe’s black mesh upper is accented with a speckled Pink Flash Swoosh at the toe, while the tonal black quarter panels are finished in a subtle reptilian texture—a hallmark feature of the Air Yeezy 2. A final design tie-in takes the form of the Fresh Mint coloring on the lightweight sole unit.

results.name: Nike Solarsoft Moccasin Woven Yeezy
results.story: Part of a series of shoes inspired by the Chinese zodiac’s Year of the Snake, this Solarsoft Moc Woven features a premium leather upper with snakeskin detailing near the laces. The forefoot sports a woven detail reminiscent of the stitching of a moccasin, and the mesh tongue panel promotes breathability. The simple colorway of the exterior is contrasted by the Challenge Red inner lining.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 950 Peyote
results.story: The Yeezy 950 Boot ‘Peyote’ was one of the four original colorways of the duck boot-military boot hybrid that launched as part of Kanye West’s Yeezy Season 1 range. The light tan hue is tonally consistent with the color story of the collection at large, which is highlighted by a dark and muddy palette. The rugged build makes use of a combination of ballistic mesh, suede and durable throughout the upper, while the outsole makes use of a high-traction rubber tread.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 700 Analog
results.story: Music and fashion icon Kanye West debuted the Yeezy Boost 700 at his Yeezy Season 5 fashion show in February 2017. This 'Analog' colorway released April 2019, and provides a monochromatic look to the acclaimed shoe. Dressed in shades of white, leather, mesh and suede panels come together to construct its upper. Down below, full-length Boost cushioning provides a responsive feel, built inside the 700's signature chunky midsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 500 High Slate
results.story: Designer Kanye West updates the 500 silhouette with the adidas Yeezy 500 High. Launched in December 2019, this makeover is set up with a Slate-colored neoprene base overlaid in paneled suede with touches of tumbled leather. Rope laces secure the tongue and a textured mudguard reinforces the sidewall. Offering contrast, the sculpted midsole holds Adiprene cushioning and undulating tread patterns the rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Arzareth
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Arzareth’ features vibrant blue tones on a breathable knit upper, its side panels overlaid with a semi-translucent RPU cage for added structure and durability. Contrasting black is applied to the sneaker’s bootie-style collar, good for a snug fit around the ankle. The sneaker rides on a PU encapsulated EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a herringbone rubber outsole for grippy traction.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Azure
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ utilizes a re-engineered Primeknit upper finished in muddy brown tones. A contrasting splash of royal blue distinguishes the translucent monofilament window that’s woven into the lateral side of the sock-like construction. Responsive cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length Boost midsole, featuring an elevated heel for a fluid transition. Underfoot, a herringbone rubber outsole provides grippy traction. The Yeezy Boost 380 ‘Azure Non-Reflective’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in Europe.

results.name: Nike Air Foamposite Pro Yeezy
results.story: Released in April of 2014, The Nike Air Foamposite Pro Prm 'Yeezy’ was inspired by Kanye West’s 2012 Nike Air Yeezy 2 NRG ‘Solar Red’ and features a design that combines a black mesh/nubuck upper with a black Foamposite shell and swoosh. The sneaker also includes bright solar red accents and sits on a glow-in-the-dark translucent green outsole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 Infants 'Hylte'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Hylte’ dresses the sneaker’s re-engineered Primeknit upper in a complementary blend of tan and yellow hues, resulting in a subtle camo-like design that’s interrupted by a streak of neon green on the translucent monofilament window. The lightweight build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole, encased in grey rubber and reinforced by a herringbone rubber outsole to provide reliable traction for little feet. The Yeezy Boost 380 Infants ‘Hylte’ is a regional exclusive and only launched in North America and Latin America.

results.name: adidas Yeezy 700 V3 Kyanite
results.story: The adidas Yeezy 700 V3 ‘Kyanite’ showcases flowing stripes of blue coloring throughout the breathable upper, constructed from monofilament engineered mesh with exoskeletal RPU overlays coated in a glow-in-the-dark finish. Interior bootie construction delivers a snug fit, while a reinforced rubber toe cap provides added durability. The sneaker rides on a lightweight EVA midsole encapsulated in an off-white PU cage, supported by a herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Quiet Grey
results.story: The adidas Yeezy PowerPhase is an expression of designer Kanye West's reverence for retro sportswear. Updated in September 2019, this Quiet Gray variation has a suede base minimally styled with perforated Three-Stripes, tonal lacing and a signature logo window. 'Calabasas' is spelled out in gold foil on the quarter panel. Its split rubber cupsole is kept standard to match the sneaker's single-hued scheme.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Powerphase Simple Brown
results.story: In September 2019, the adidas Yeezy PowerPhase was reintroduced in a three colorway collection designed around Kanye West's trademark selection of earth tones. A Simple Brown shade is draped across this variation's suede upper, mesh lining and laces. Contrast comes from the retro logo window and metallic 'Calabasas' lettering alongside the Three-Stripes. The classic rubber cupsole is positioned below for support.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 380 'Triple Black'
results.story: The Yeezy Boost 380 further showcases Kanye West's low-top sneaker design with a modified profile and technical motif. This 'Black' edition features a dark Primeknit upper with reflective elements, circular perforations and flecked laces. As established through previous Yeezy releases, this edition includes a full-length adidas Boost unit encapsulated within semi-translucent rubber. The shoe is finished with a tightly treaded outsole and a small Three-Stripes icon at the heel.

results.name: Yeezy Slides Kids 'Desert Sand'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Desert Sand’ combines plush comfort with a futuristic, minimalist design, executed on a lightweight EVA build and finished in a refined hue. The unibody upper is stripped of any exterior branding, save for adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the cushioned footbed. An aggressive traction pattern distinguishes the outsole, delivering optimal grip and impact absorption underfoot.

results.name: adidas Yeezy Desert Boot Oil
results.story: Borrowing the suede toe box and oval overlays from the Yeezy 500, 2019's Yeezy Desert Boot 'Oil' takes Kanye West's signature line into boot territory. The three-quarter cut upper comes in a smooth suede and mesh, with thick rope laces and an exaggerated mudguard. The chunky foam midsole pairs with a thick rugged outsole for outdoors-ready cushioning and traction. The entire silhouette comes in an earth-toned motif, with just a bit of branding on the bottom of the sole.

results.name: Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Light'
results.story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Light’ updates the minimalist sneaker with UV-sensitive technology, a first for Kanye West’s lifestyle imprint. Under artificial light, the Primeknit upper projects a subtle ivory finish. Exposure to direct sunlight yields soft pink coloring throughout the knit build, while the monofilament side stripe darkens to an amber hue. The color-shifting assembly is supported by a standard rubber-wrapped Boost midsole.
